headline: Holy Cross Student Rower Killed in Florida Crash
abstract: According to the college, Grace Rett, 20, died when a pickup slammed into a van carrying about a dozen members of the team.
lead_paragraph: A student at College of the Holy Cross in Massachusetts on her way to rowing practice in Florida was killed Wednesday morning when a pickup slammed into a passenger van carrying several members of the womenâ€™s crew team, according to local authorities and the college.
